The paper deals with optimizing signal constellations for communication systems in the presence of phase noise, which is a common problem in wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also involves optimization techniques and analysis of communication channels, which are relevant to cs.COMM (Communication and Networking). The paper may also be relevant to cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control), as these categories deal with various aspects of communication systems.
